etirement accounts count at 60-70% of actual value typically. Calculate total needs with the<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/closing-cost-calculator/"> closing cost calculator</a> including reserves.</p><h3><b>How long does self employed mortgage approval take?</b></h3><p>Self employed approvals require 35-50 days from application to final closing. Traditional W-2 borrowers close in 30-40 days typically for comparison. Additional time stems from business documentation review complexity throughout.</p><p>Bank statement programs sometimes close faster at 25-35 days total. Statements clearly show qualifying income without extensive underwriter analysis. DSCR loans close in 20-30 days focusing only on property performance.</p><p>Front-load documentation organization saving weeks before formal applications begin. Gather two years of tax returns, bank statements, and business licenses. Schedule consultation at<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/"> Stairway Mortgage</a> for timeline guidance.</p><h3><b>What if I have multiple business entities?</b></h3><p>Multiple business entities complicate traditional qualification significantly with combined analysis. S-corporations, LLCs, and Schedule C activities all require documentation. Each entity contributes proportionate income to total qualification calculation.</p><p>Bank statement programs simplify by analyzing aggregate deposits across entities. Combined business income appears in personal or business bank statements. This eliminates complex entity income allocation calculations completely.</p><p>Asset-based programs ignore business structures entirely focusing on liquid assets. Entity complexity becomes irrelevant when qualifying through investment portfolios. Explore<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/portfolio-loan/"> portfolio loan flexibility</a> for complex situations.</p><h3><b>Can seasonal businesses qualify for mortgages?</b></h3><p>Seasonal businesses show signi